{"word":"ἐπακούω","slug":"ἐπακούω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπακούω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ακούσομαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to listen</i> or <i>hearken to, to hear</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, attic: also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei et <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to hear</i> a thing <i>from</i> a person, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to give ear, hearken</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to obey</i>, <el>τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}